11 people with bounties
over 100 million?!

309
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:14,370
Yes.

310
00:16:14,940 --> 00:16:19,580
Excluding Monkey-chan and Roronoa-chan,
that still leaves nine.

311
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:22,970
When you entered the Grand Line,

312
00:16:22,970 --> 00:16:26,560
you chose one of seven routes

313
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:29,320
and followed your Log all the way here.

314
00:16:29,490 --> 00:16:30,510
Yeah.

315
00:16:30,510 --> 00:16:33,580
So, naturally, there are others

316
00:16:33,580 --> 00:16:36,320
who took one of the six other routes
and had to overcome many difficulties

317
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:38,280
similar to yours to get here.

318
00:16:38,900 --> 00:16:42,620
All routes run into the Red Line,

319
00:16:42,620 --> 00:16:47,060
so everyone gathers on this
archipelago to cross that wall.

320
00:16:47,730 --> 00:16:48,790
Understand?

321
00:16:49,080 --> 00:16:53,370
It's not every day
that so many of the world's rookies

322
00:16:53,370 --> 00:16:55,860
all show up at the same time, though...

323
00:16:57,080 --> 00:16:59,760
Especially Kid, Luffy,

324
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:02,290
Hawkins, Drake, Law...

325
00:17:02,900 --> 00:17:06,800
These names showed up
in newspapers all the time.

326
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:08,000
I don't read newspapers.

327
00:17:09,550 --> 00:17:11,190
Information is a weapon.

328
00:17:11,660 --> 00:17:14,380
Shouldn't you at least learn
the names of your rivals?

329
00:17:14,620 --> 00:17:18,320
Let's see... Kid, Hawkins, and...

330
00:17:18,320 --> 00:17:19,430
Drake, was it?

331
00:17:19,850 --> 00:17:22,300
In terms of bounty amounts...

332
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:25,140
you'd be #2.

333
00:17:25,660 --> 00:17:27,420
There's someone worth more than Luffy?!

334
00:17:27,420 --> 00:17:28,400
On these islands?!

335
00:17:33,450 --> 00:17:36,400
"Grove #24 - Restaurant"

336
00:17:44,670 --> 00:17:46,250
Look at her eat!

337
00:17:46,560 --> 00:17:49,130
Where does all the food go?!

338
00:17:49,820 --> 00:17:52,540
Bring more food!

339
00:17:54,290 --> 00:17:56,420
Vulgar woman...

340
00:17:58,470 --> 00:18:00,970
She's ruining my meal.

341
00:18:01,380 --> 00:18:02,850
Go shut her up.

342
00:18:03,060 --> 00:18:05,060
That's not a good idea, Father!

343
00:18:05,060 --> 00:18:07,230
Navy Headquarters is just
a stone's throw away!

344
00:18:07,790 --> 00:18:09,230
If we were to cause a scene now...!

345
00:18:13,340 --> 00:18:19,860
"From West Blue Captain
of the Firetank Pirates"

346
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:16,000
Capone "Gang" Bege.

347
00:18:16,380 --> 00:18:19,860
A 138 million Berry bounty.

348
00:18:20,960 --> 00:18:22,520
Where's my seconds?!

349
00:18:22,950 --> 00:18:25,130
Bring it now!

350
00:18:25,890 --> 00:18:29,620
T-They said they're working
as hard as they can, Captain.

351
00:18:29,930 --> 00:18:32,250
It's not fast enough!

352
00:18:33,080 --> 00:18:35,880
More pizzas!

353
00:18:36,260 --> 00:18:43,350
"From South Blue Captain
of the Bonney Pirates"

354
00:18:37,310 --> 00:18:39,450
Jewelry Bonney, the "Glutton".

355
00:18:39,880 --> 00:18:43,350
A 140 million Berry bounty.

356
00:18:44,740 --> 00:18:46,590
I'll bring it right away!

357
00:18:48,130 --> 00:18:49,940
I-I'm very sorry!

358
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:55,760
Why, you little...!

359
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:57,360
Stop.

360
00:18:58,260 --> 00:18:59,860
Why, Captain?!

361
00:19:00,140 --> 00:19:03,160
He got spaghetti all over my clothes!

362
00:19:03,610 --> 00:19:06,290
Such was the fate of those clothes.

363
00:19:06,900 --> 00:19:09,220
I apologize for scaring you.

364
00:19:09,450 --> 00:19:13,040
Taking a life on this particular day
will only diminish fortuity.

365
00:19:13,450 --> 00:19:20,680
"From North Blue Captain
of the Hawkins Pirates"

366
00:19:14,420 --> 00:19:16,830
Basil Hawkins, the "Magician."

367
00:19:17,050 --> 00:19:20,680
A 249 million Berry bounty.

368
00:19:25,890 --> 00:19:28,180
Who's the guy with the stupid face?

369
00:19:28,460 --> 00:19:31,620
Oh, that'd be Sea Roar.

370
00:19:35,960 --> 00:19:36,570
Boss!

371
00:19:44,380 --> 00:19:45,740
What's going on?! A fight?!

372
00:19:46,650 --> 00:19:50,490
If you want a fight,
let's save it for the other side!

373
00:19:52,290 --> 00:19:56,090
Or do you not know how strong I am?

374
00:19:56,460 --> 00:20:03,930
"From Grand Line (Longarm Tribe)
Captain of On Air Pirates"

375
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:59,880
Scratchmen Apoo, the "Sea Roar."

376
00:20:00,130 --> 00:20:03,930
A 198 million Berry bounty.

377
00:20:05,380 --> 00:20:08,600
Then quit yer damn starin'.

378
00:20:08,910 --> 00:20:10,480
Boss! Don't!

379
00:20:11,090 --> 00:20:13,620
Damn, you're one creepy bastard.

380
00:20:14,130 --> 00:20:16,770
I can get rid of you
right now, if you'd like!

381
00:20:17,010 --> 00:20:24,570
"From South Blue
Captain of the Kid Pirates"

382
00:20:18,080 --> 00:20:20,260
Eustass "Captain" Kid.

383
00:20:20,780 --> 00:20:24,570
A 315 million Berry bounty.

384
00:20:29,550 --> 00:20:31,450
The Mad Monk's on a rampage!

385
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:36,040
We gotta get outta here, quick!

386
00:20:55,360 --> 00:20:56,520
If you wanna go wild...

387
00:20:57,670 --> 00:20:59,180
...do it in the New World!

388
00:20:59,850 --> 00:21:06,860
"From North Blue
Captain of the Drake Pirates"

389
00:21:01,060 --> 00:21:03,310
"Red Flag" X. Drake.

390
00:21:03,590 --> 00:21:06,860
A 222 million Berry bounty.

391
00:21:09,940 --> 00:21:10,870
I see.

392
00:21:12,410 --> 00:21:14,790
Drake, the fallen navy officer...

393
00:21:15,910 --> 00:21:22,130
"From Sky Island
Captain of the Fallen Monk Pirates"

394
00:21:17,070 --> 00:21:18,880
"Mad Monk" Urouge.

395
00:21:19,310 --> 00:21:22,130
A 180 million Berry bounty.

396
00:21:23,340 --> 00:21:27,050
You're lucky to be alive, masked fellow.

397
00:21:27,230 --> 00:21:34,310
"From South Blue
Combat Crewman for the Kid Pirates"

398
00:21:28,330 --> 00:21:30,460
Killer, the "Massacre Soldier."

399
00:21:30,730 --> 00:21:34,310
A 162 million Berry bounty.

400
00:21:40,780 --> 00:21:43,280
Things were just getting good, too...

401
00:21:45,190 --> 00:21:46,530
Drake-ya...

402
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:49,820
How many people have you killed?

403
00:21:50,110 --> 00:21:56,580
"From North Blue
Captain of the Heart Pirates"

404
00:21:51,010 --> 00:21:54,030
Trafalgar Law, the Surgeon of Death.

405
00:21:54,300 --> 00:21:56,580
A 200 million Berry bounty.

406
00:22:02,350 --> 00:22:06,340
A countless number of pirates
have entered the Grand Line,

407
00:22:06,340 --> 00:22:08,480
but only a countable few
have made it this far.

408
00:22:09,590 --> 00:22:13,630
The Grand Line is a lot like
an enormous survival tournament.

409
00:22:13,830 --> 00:22:16,860
Those pirates who've made it
this far through each route alive

410
00:22:16,860 --> 00:22:19,440
are truly the cream of the crop.

411
00:22:19,820 --> 00:22:21,450
One of them

412
00:22:21,450 --> 00:22:25,630
might even usher
in the next generation of pirates.

413
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:27,920
In any case,

414
00:22:27,920 --> 00:22:30,960
with so many rookies here
all at the same time,

415
00:22:30,960 --> 00:22:33,330
things are going to get ugly
in the New World.

416
00:22:33,570 --> 00:22:37,500
Also, as for why Captain Kid's
bounty is higher than yours...

417
00:22:38,700 --> 00:22:41,940
It's because he causes
serious harm to civilians.

418
00:22:42,500 --> 00:22:44,300
Not very charming, is he?

419
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:49,300
That's why I'm behind you guys 100%.

420
00:22:49,690 --> 00:22:52,250
Well, for now...

421
00:22:52,710 --> 00:22:54,440
I just wanna have fun!

422
00:22:58,560 --> 00:23:02,070
But I'm worried about
the old craftsman guy,

423
00:23:02,070 --> 00:23:03,150
if he's in such a rough town.

424
00:23:04,810 --> 00:23:06,820
My husband will be fine.

425
00:23:08,490 --> 00:23:11,870
After all, he's 100 times
stronger than you kids...

426
00:23:12,900 --> 00:23:14,380
100...

427
00:23:14,490 --> 00:23:15,430
...times?

428
00:23:25,460 --> 00:23:28,420
Right! We're gonna go find the old coating guy!

429
00:23:28,420 --> 00:23:29,420
Yeah!

430
00:23:29,420 --> 00:23:30,930
Oh! It's the Sabaody Park!

431
00:23:30,930 --> 00:23:32,740
Let's try looking here for him!

432
00:23:32,740 --> 00:23:36,020
Yeah! He might be hiding in the ferris wheel!

433
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:37,960
Alright, let's have fun!

434
00:23:37,960 --> 00:23:40,230
You're not trying to find him!

435
00:23:40,230 --> 00:23:41,500
On the next episode of One Piece!

436
00:23:41,500 --> 00:23:44,750
"The Target is Camie!! The Looming
Clutches of a Professional Kidnapper"

437
00:23:45,020 --> 00:23:47,010
I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
